The whole point of said fortresses, was to hold out and deny the use of
nearby transport routes. Superheavy howitzers could and did defeat them,
but were fairly beastly items to move and supply: and taking Verdun by
armed action, as seen in 1916, was no easy task. Otherwise, they were
built and stored to hold out for a while... and if you're trying to
smash the fortresses around Verdun you're committing troops and
resources that are no longer available elsewhere. (The whole point of
the Schlieffen Plan was, after all, to _avoid_ those fortifications)

