There wasn't any other way to move supplies over distance at the time.
Recall that what motor transport was available, had been massively
overused already with the inevitable problems of breakdowns, shortages
of fuel and spares, and driver exhaustion.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt;As long as the French were holding on
&gt;from Verdun to Belfort, there were very few routes from Germany to France
&gt;_except_ via Belgium, either by rail or any other way. But it looks to me as
